{
  "doc_id": "55406",
  "text": "The concentrations of PAHs in different grades of coffee are different, with lower content in green coffee. Benzo(a)pyrene was not found in green coffee at all. The most amount of benzo(a)pyrene was determined in instant coffee and in roasted coffee. It was shown that the content of benzo(a)pyrene depends on the roasting degree [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Typically, benzo(a)pyrene served as an indicator of the overall contamination of coffee with PAHs.",
